	(5, '22°18′12″', '103°46′30', 'Fansipan', '1', '', 1, '2800m camping point.', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Fansipan, also known in the vernacular, is Hủa Xi Pan, meaning giant stone slab. With an altitude of 3,143m, this is the highest mountain in all 3 Indochina countries; at the same time, it is also a mountain range with the most complex terrain in the region. Fansipan is a huge granite block that was discovered deep into the earth thanks to specific geological tectonic activity more than 250 million years ago. Viewed from above, the entire peak of the "big brother" mountain is like a hand suddenly reaching up from the deep green forest surface, reaching out to the cloudy sky. No one knows exactly: Who was the first person to paint and break the stone to find the way to the top of the sky? There is also no accurate record of how arduous and difficult the journey to reach the roof of Indochina was. The silvery traces of history have been covered by the dust of time for hundreds of years. The only thing that remains corroborated is the level of... horror of the old forest road.', 'd'),
	(6, '22°18′12″', '103°46′30', 'Fansipan', '3', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/04f14883b7acb31768fdfb1867765e36.jpg', 2, '2800m camping point.', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Fansipan, also known in the vernacular, is Hủa Xi Pan, meaning giant stone slab. With an altitude of 3,143m, this is the highest mountain in all 3 Indochina countries; at the same time, it is also a mountain range with the most complex terrain in the region. Fansipan is a huge granite block that was discovered deep into the earth thanks to specific geological tectonic activity more than 250 million years ago. Viewed from above, the entire peak of the "big brother" mountain is like a hand suddenly reaching up from the deep green forest surface, reaching out to the cloudy sky. No one knows exactly: Who was the first person to paint and break the stone to find the way to the top of the sky? There is also no accurate record of how arduous and difficult the journey to reach the roof of Indochina was. The silvery traces of history have been covered by the dust of time for hundreds of years. The only thing that remains corroborated is the level of... horror of the old forest road.', 'd'),
	(7, '22°37′38″', '102° 47′ 8.67', 'Pusilung', '3', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/a3d28f87524cabceafdd26ad348ccb79.jpg', 2, ' Milestone No. 42', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Pu Si Lung is a mountain located on the border of Vietnam and China 3073m high The Vietnamese part of the mountain belongs to Pa Ve Su commune, Muong Tè district, Lai Chau province', 'd'),
	(8, '22°26′4″', '103°32′10″', 'Putaleng', '3', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/f140acd5d20ac845d8331f105574473f.jpg', 2, 'Vacation shack', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'The 3,049-meter-high Putaleng mountain is located in Ta Leng Commune, Tam Duong District, Lai Chau Province.', 'd'),
	(9, '22° 30′ 27.62″', '103° 35′ 14.98″', 'Bạch Mộc Lương Tử', '3', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/d9dfbdaf4b790ca322313b2f45cbd645.jpg', 2, 'camped at an altitude of 2100m', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Ky Quan San, also known as Bach Moc Luong Tu is the highest peak in the mountain range of the same name on the border between Bat Xat district of Lao Cai province and Phong Tho district of Lai Chau province, Vietnam. With an altitude of 3046m, this is the fourth highest peak in Vietnam', 'd'),
	(10, '22°26′4″', '103°32′10″', 'Tả liên sơn', '2', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/5d1b7ddfe960e71662fe8e43d3491e07.jpg', 2, 'camping', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Ta Lien is also known as Buffalo Neck. The recorded elevation on Ta Lien peak is 2996m above sea level.', 'd'),
	(11, '21° 28′ 11.12″', '104° 22′ 36.88″', 'Tà chì nhù', '2', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/15cf07bfdb4b3f55d591ffd2fab345ab.jpg', 1, 'camping at an altitude of 2400m', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Ta Lead Nhù, also known as Phu Song Sung in the thai ethnic way or Chung Chua Nha in the name of the Mong ethnic people, is a mountain peak located in Ga tu district, Yen Bai province, Vietnam. Lead Nhù has an altitude of 2,979m above sea level', 'd'),
	(12, '22° 36′ 6″', '10° 44′ 44″', 'Nhìu cồ san', '1', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/b8af3b60268049228d412b5ab2034c72.jpg', 1, 'no', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Nhiu Co San or Nhi Co San is one of the top 10 highest mountains in Vietnam (with an altitude of 2,965m). This peak belongs to Nhiu Co San village, Bat Xat district, Lao Cai province.', 'd'),
	(13, '22°18′12″', '103°46′30', 'Fansipan', '3', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/3ad88355be6a1368f1c8b7039bf9a7c4.jpg', 2, '2800m camping point.', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Trekking Fansipan is going to be a journey for visitors to challenge, to break through their limits. During the Fansipan trekking tour 2 days and 1 night, visitors will admire the majestic Hoang Lien range kneeling on top of each other in the green of mountains and forests, full of majestic clouds and touching the roof of Indochina.', NULL),
	(14, '22°26′4″', '103°32′10″', 'Pusilung', '3', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/76d66cf96766ed83cb154a4f0c942cc8.jpg', 2, ' Milestone No. 42', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Bach Moc Peak with an altitude of 3046m is the 4th highest mountain of Vietnam, the natural boundary of 2 provinces Lai Chau and Lao Cai.  It can be said that "dawn in the clouds" has become the brand of the mountain named Bach Moc. The terrain of Bach Moc is quite diverse and difficult, requiring you to prepare skills and good physical foundation. However, the value of the beautiful scenery here is always commensurate with the effort that you have to spend when conquering this peak.', NULL),
	(15, '22°37′38″', '102° 47′ 8.67', 'Tả liên sơn', '3', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/d525d7c069e0aee1547914114d026c92.jpg', 2, 'Vacation shack', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'experience the journey through the primeval forest in Tam Duong district, Lai Chau province. Pu Ta Leng\'s specialty is the cool streams and thousands of azaleas every spring.', NULL),
	(16, '22° 30′ 27.62″', '103° 35′ 14.98″', 'Putaleng', '2', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/3ad95b9b982f01ab8a6c995d55dee07a.jpg', 2, 'camped at an altitude of 2100m', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'The journey to conquer Pusilung will definitely bring arduous challenges and bring memorable experiences. The route climbs along large streams with many rapids. When you reach an altitude of 2800m, you will encounter mark 42 – one of the highest border milestones of Vietnam. From the 42nd mark, there are nearly 17km more forest roads to reach the top. ', NULL),
	(17, '22° 30′ 27.62″', '103° 35′ 14.98″', 'Putaleng', '2', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/b0697546225ecbe0470447707b2f95e3.jpg', 2, 'camped at an altitude of 2100m', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'The journey to conquer Pusilung will definitely bring arduous challenges and bring memorable experiences. The route climbs along large streams with many rapids. When you reach an altitude of 2800m, you will encounter mark 42 – one of the highest border milestones of Vietnam. From the 42nd mark, there are nearly 17km more forest roads to reach the top. ', 'd'),
	(18, '22° 30′ 27.62″', '103° 35′ 14.98″', 'Tả liên sơn', '2', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/b96de7e870bf05449d9940cd455772b6.jpg', 2, 'camping', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'experience the journey through the primeval forest in Tam Duong district, Lai Chau province. Pu Ta Leng\'s specialty is the cool streams and thousands of azaleas every spring.', 'd'),
	(19, '21° 28′ 11.12″', '104° 22′ 36.88″', 'Bạch Mộc Lương Tử', '1', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/49e416e5dad475ebb10ccc36f1057e2a.jpg', 2, 'camping at an altitude of 2400m', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'the top of the mountain is as proud as the spine of the buffalo living in the forest at the foot of the mountain, so Ta Lien is also known as The Buffalo Neck. The recorded elevation on Ta Lien peak is 2996m above sea level. From above, you can see the small but beautiful city of Lai Chau among four majestic mountains and forests.  Ta Lien forest with diverse primary vegetation will make you overwhelmed and excited. You seem to get lost in the mysterious fairytale scene with ancient trees, moss and ferns covered, creeping trunks clinging to stone slabs stacked with all sorts of strange shapes, carpets of white fallen camellias, fiery red maple leaves and green moss carpets that charm a fresh color.', NULL),
	(20, '22° 36′ 6″', '10° 44′ 44″', 'Tà chì nhù', '1', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/48612aa0cec067b681a646b327b7832b.jpg', 1, 'camping at an altitude of 2400m', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Bach Moc Peak with an altitude of 3046m is the 4th highest mountain of Vietnam, the natural boundary of 2 provinces Lai Chau and Lao Cai.  It can be said that "dawn in the clouds" has become the brand of the mountain named Bach Moc. The terrain of Bach Moc is quite diverse and difficult, requiring you to prepare skills and good physical foundation. However, the value of the beautiful scenery here is always commensurate with the effort that you have to spend when conquering this peak.', NULL),
	(21, '22° 36′ 6″', '103°46′30', 'Nhìu Cồ San', '1', '../admin/assets/img/Mountaineering/82a94236cb17ac0a897f3bf17c00be9a.jpg', 1, ' Milestone No. 42', 'Hiking Boots,Clothing,identification,food', 'Nhiu Co San or Nhi Co San is one of the top 10 highest mountains in Vietnam (with an altitude of 2,965m). This peak belongs to Nhiu Co San village, Bat Xat district, Lao Cai province.', NULL);

